ul.li:
annotated_3d_model_equivalence_criteria schema: provides representations of equivalence validation criteria
 for annotated 3d model data together with the pertaining inspection requirements, 
 assessment specifications and thresholds for judging whether, or not, equivalence is satisfied;

inscope.li:
representation of equivalence validation criteria for annotated 3d model data coupled with the inspection requirements
            for the evaluation of criteria, and with the pertinent assessment specifications;
            Equivalence validation criteria can be used for the representation of requirements on equivalence,
                             declaration of equivalence, and assurance of equivalence of two annotated 3d model data.
                             The target shape model data are conformant to those defined in ISO 10303-42[2], or application protocol
                             based on ISO 10303-42;

ul.li:
Necessary conditions for appropriate inspection shall be clarified such as mandatory inspection process if 
                    definable, what physical quantity shall be inspected, what special cases shall be considered and required 
                    precision of inspection result;

The most basic case is the case when calculation of a physical quantity is required as a preparation for comparison. 
    For doing this, a space where pertaining metric is unique and product data representation is unique is required. 
    ISO 10303 representation will be a single reasonable space for dealing with this case;
